1987 following a bitter lockout by ibp the strike ended last july 
the fine is the second largest osha has ever imposed against an 
individual company the largest was 42 million against bath iron 
works in bath maine in november 1987 for health and safety 
violations 
the largest fine against multiple companies came in march of 
this year 511 million against five contractors that worked on a 
brideport conn apartment building that collapsed in april 1987 
