the 50kiloton device equivalent to 50000 tons of dynamite 
went off at 5 am at a nuclear test site on the frenchcontrolled 
mururua atoll about onethird of the way between new zealand and 
the central american coast 
the explosion was the 92nd underground test there since france 
abandoned atmospheric testing in 1975 said to warwick smith 
director of the new zealand seismological observatory in wellington 
the new zealand government will keep expressing its strong 
concern about french nuclear testing whenever it occurs said new 
