china the worlds leading hog producer has 
ended pork rationing according to an agriculture department report 
a chinese agriculture official privately stated that pork 
rationing in beijing had stopped being enforced the departments 
foreign agricultural service said wednesday other officials said 
that pork rationing had ended throughout the country though no 
official announcement has confirmed this 
china began rationing pork in most major cities last fall in 
response to shortages pork traditionally supplies about 80 percent 
of the total animal protein in the chinese diet 
the pork shortages that led to the rationing did not however 
affect chinas ability to supply hogs to its limited export markets 
primarily hong kong the report said in fact the country 
has had a surplus of hogs for export to hong kong but increases in 
hog trade between the two countries has been limited by a chinese 
export quota 
an end to rationing shows that chinese agricultural officials 
believe the tight pork supply situation is now being resolved as 
producers respond to lower feed prices higher pork prices and 
government incentives to promote larger production the report said 
it also is an indication that many urban consumers are willing 
to pay more for the higherquality free market pork instead of 
enduring the cheaper fattier meat that has been sold at lower 
prices in state markets the report said 
a usda study last year showed that china had a 1983 yearend 
inventory of 2985 million hogs compared with 558 million in the 
united states 
but with more than five times the number of hogs chinas pork 
production was less than double the us output 132 million 
metric tons to 76 million tons the usda study said a metric ton 
is about 2205 pounds 
the reason it took only six months for an american farmer to 
raise a 243pound hog ready for slaughter while a newborn chinese 
pig can take from eight to 18 months to reach a comparable 
slaughter weight 
also the study said the average us hog will produce a 
dressedout carcass of about 173 pounds compared with the chinese 
carcass of about 140 pounds 
