tabatha foster the chubbycheeked tot who 
smiled despite adversity won the hearts of many and her 
supporters say her fight following a historic fiveorgan transplant 
reveals more about life and courage than about medicine 
through her god touched the world her uncle james foster 
said thursday he said look yall think you got problems well 
look at this girl look what she has done it brought the highest 
and the lowest people together for just a minute 
tabatha 3 of madisonville ky died wednesday afternoon in 
the intensive care unit of childrens hospital of pittsburgh after 
an infection in her bloodstream caused her heart kidneys and liver 
to fail 
the 36pound pigtailed child was the worlds longest survivor 
of a fiveorgan transplant she received a new liver small 
intestines pancreas and parts of a stomach and colon during a 
15hour experimental operation that ended nov 1 
similar procedures had been performed only twice before and 
both patients died within a few days 
you couldnt help but love that little girl so many of us 
learned so much from her and not just medically said hospital 
spokeswoman sue cardillo 
tabatha was never down she said when people ask if the 
operation was a success its hard to measure success it was a 
success because tabatha lived six additional months and there were 
good times 
because of an intestinal deformity doctors had been forced to 
remove 95 percent of tabathas small bowel three days after she was 
born she was placed on a highly concentrated liquid diet which 
damaged her own liver 
doctors had said tabatha would soon die without the transplant 
she was hospitalized for all but seven weeks of her life and 
though she said she craved pizza the only solid food she ever ate 
was rice cereal ms cardillo said 
tabatha won the affection of hospital staff with goodnatured 
teasing playing peekaboo and singing the itsybitsy spider 
she walked through hospital halls with an intravenous pole in tow 
wearing her cherished tennis shoes and chatting with anyone 
tabathas hospital room was empty thursday the countless 
stuffed animals tons and tons of cards and a photo of a puppy 
recently given to tabatha have been packed in boxes ms cardillo 
said 
i think its affected everybody in the hospital from 
housekeeping on up at every level heartstrings are being pulled 
ms cardillo said 
tabathas parents roy and sandra foster quickly checked out of 
pittsburghs ronald mcdonald house where they had stayed for 
months ms cardillo said they did not want their whereabouts known 
thursday as they prepared to leave for home 
other family members gathered in madisonville waiting for the 
parents to join them and remembering tabatha 
she had those fat jaws and was always smiling foster 33 
said in a telephone interview she was a survivor she was a 
fighter 
tabathas aunt doris east 41 of huntsville ala said the 
child taught her to have faith 
she taught me to endure because she did she said 
ms east said the family was grateful the transplant kept 
tabatha alive for a time 
they gave her another day she said it just gave us more 
time with her 
foster said it was amazing tabatha won the affection of people 
like president reagan who had mentioned tabathas plight in a 
national radio address in january and contributed 1000 toward her 
medical expenses 
wellwishers from around the country including frank sinatra 
donated more than 350000 to help cover medical expenses for 
tabatha much of the money came from black churches tabatha was 
black 
tabatha foster showed us that courage and strength come in all 
sizes kentucky gov wallace g wilkinson said 
