the issue said surveys show that most parents would identify drug 
abuse and kidnapping as the major concerns about their childs 
safety 
dodd said 67 children in the united state were abducted last 
year and 57 died from drug abuse while nearly 8000 children aged 
14 and under were killed and 50000 were permanently disabled as a 
result of avoidable accidents 
according to the department of health and human services nearly 
half the deaths of children aged 14 and under are caused by 
unintentional injuries 
the safe kids campaign was developed by childrens hospital in 
washington and is supported by johnson amp johnson co and the 
national safety council surgeon general c everett koop serves as 
honorary chairman of the national campaign 
more than 40 health corporate and childrens organizations have 
joined the campaign with president reagan expected to sign a 
proclamation designating may 1622 as national safe kids week 
public service announcements featuring ms post will begin 
airing nationwide on monday inviting listeners to call 
800365kids to request a 16page safety booklet 
the publication advises parents on how to protect children from 
injury in five leading risk areas traffic accidents drownings 
burns and scalds choking and poisoning and falls 
the booklet also urges parents to take first aid and 
cardiopulmonary resuscitation courses to enable them to provide 
immediate proper care if an injury does occur 
safe kids groups in 24 cities will host injury prevention 
activities next week 
this campaign has set an ambitious goal to change the way 
america thinks about and deals with the epidemic of preventable 
injuries to children said herta burbach feely executive 
director of the campaign 
the fact is we have not done and we are not doing everything 
that we can to prevent childhood injuries either as individuals 
the community or as a nation 
