<TEXT>
chinese herbs and antiseptics are the 
newest weapons in the war against cavities and gum disease 
researchers said thursday 
theyre as common as the common cold university of maryland 
dental school microbiologist barbara margaret said of gum problems 
and tooth decay 
speaking at the 88th annual convention of the american society 
for microbiology she said her study involved having patients with 
gum disease dip special toothbrushes in a mild prescription 
antibiotic called chlordexidine and then brush 
within one to three weeks plaquecausing bacteria decreased 
she said 
this is an attempt to combine treatments a mechanical cleaning 
with the use of a mild antiseptic she said the upanddown 
scraping dislodge the bacteria 
the seven patients in the test group used tiny 
christmastreeshaped brushes designed to get the antibiotic 
solution in pockets of infection near tooth roots they use the 
technique in conjunction with regular brushing said margaret who 
hopes to soon launch a larger study 
extracts of plants used in chinese folk medicine also appear 
promising in the fight against tooth decay and gum disease said 
university of colorado microbiologist christine wuyuan 
she started her research after a 1984 trip to taiwan where 
dentists prescribe herbs for patients 
they know it works but they dont know why it works she 
said chinese folk medicine is rich with plantderived products 
used to treat gum disease and maintain oral health we looked at 
herbs that can affect cavities and gum disease 
she pulverized 40 kinds of plants that she found in chinese 
markets in chicago and san francisco and mixed the extracts with 
bacteria commonly found in mouths 
fortytwo percent of the extracts inhibited bacterial growth 
including 10 percent that outright killed the germs she said 
she refused to name the plants used saying corporations are 
pressing her for that information 
ms wuyuan said the next step is further research on the 
promising extracts using patients instead of bacteria and 
finetuning the amounts that could be used in a toothpaste or 
mouthwash 
a lot of the time with gum disease there are no symptoms so 
people dont take it seriously until their teeth are in danger of 
falling out she said 
