<TEXT>
the senate on thursday easily rejected the 
latest attempt to have the chamber express a formal opinion on 
president reagans expanded policy of protecting shipping in the 
wartorn persian gulf 
the senate voted 8213 to table and thus kill an amendment to 
a pentagon budget bill that would have required a report from 
reagan outlining his policy 
the proposal would have required specifics about the us goals 
anticipated length of deployment and the rules under which us 
weapons would be fired 
the plan was offered by sen brock adams dwash who again 
criticized his colleagues for refusing to vote on whether the 
senate approves of reagans yearold policy 
adams a critic of the administration policy told his fellow 
senators that for over a year we have danced around the issues 
reagans policy involves having the navy protect 11 reflagged 
kuwaiti tankers in the gulf which has been the scene of fighting 
in the long iraniraq war kuwait is an iraqi ally 
the us policy recently was expanded to provide american 
protection to neutral merchant ships who are attacked and who seek 
us help from navy warships 
that expanded policy came in the wake of an april 18 clash 
between the navy and iran in which the navy sank or damaged six 
iranian vessels it was the latest in a series of military fights 
between the navy and iran 
congress has yet to vote formal approval or disapproval of 
reagans policy the senate also has rejected adams repeated 
efforts to invoke the war powers act that is the 1973 law that 
would under some circumstances require the withdrawal of us 
forces from situations of imminent danger 
reagan has refused to invoke the war powers law arguing that it 
is an unconstitutional restriction on his authority adams and 110 
other legislators have sued to invoke the law but a federal judge 
rejected the suit and they are appealing that rejection 
sen john warner rva a former secretary of the navy led the 
opposition to adams proposal 
