a handful of dramatic films offer hope for adult audiences 
francis coppola returns with his longplanned tucker with jeff 
bridges as the inventor who tries to revolutionize the automobile 
industry tom berenger and debra winger star in betrayed about 
an fbi agent who infiltrates a midwest hate group 
that nearly extinct species the western gets another chance 
for revival with young guns whose cast include emilio estevez 
charlie sheen kiefer sutherland and lou diamond phillips 
and for the small fry the new adventures of pippi 
longstocking and a revival of disneys bambi 
how does the summer season look to movie buyers 
i think its going to be willow rambo and crocodile 
dundee said todd zsmania booker for the 75screen mescop chain 
in michigan and wisconsin 
i saw a rough cut of willow that was a little slow getting 
started then picked up speed i assume they made some cuts and i 
think it will be a winner i also saw a rough cut of crocodile 
and the ending was confused but i think theyll take care of that 
