company can be obligated to pay retired and laidoff workers 
navistar is accused of selling the moneylosing steel unit in 
1977 to envirodyne inc a los angelesbased engineering company 
with no steelmaking experience in a bid free itself of 
multimilliondollar pension payouts and other employeebenefit 
obligations 
in a trial scheduled to begin today before us district judge 
