<TEXT>
pan american world airways and aeroflot begin 
the first nonstop service between new york and moscow this weekend 
under a joint venture pan am announced thursday 
the first flight from john f kennedy international airport will 
leave at 545 pm edt saturday and arrive at sheremetyevo airport 
at 1055 am sunday morning local time pan am stated 
the first flight from moscow will leave sunday at 120 pm 
local time and arrive at jfk at 250 pm edt 
under terms of the joint venture which was approved at the 
december summit meeting between president reagan and soviet leader 
mikhail gorbachev pan am and aeroflot individually will market and 
sell onehalf of the passenger and cargo space and share equally in 
the cost of operation 
the flights will use pan am boeing 747s staffed by pan am 
cockpit and flight service crews aeroflot may provide up to three 
flight attendants for interpretation and marketing 
there will be three flights a week in the summer two in spring 
and fall and one a week in the winter pan am said 
